<subSubSection id="F8996556FF87FFB3FF11BBFAFA4BF85B" box="[199,1437,1987,2012]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B03C36DDFF87FFB3FF11BBFAFA4BF85B" blockId="0.[151,1437,1049,2012]" box="[199,1437,1987,2012]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="82F7EACFFF87FFB3FF11BBFAFEEAF85C" bold="true" box="[199,316,1987,2011]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="77834D5EFF87FFB3FDAEBBFDFC19F85B" authority="Zheng et al, 2017" authorityName="Zheng et al" authorityYear="2017" box="[632,975,1988,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Mongolotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hubeiensis">
<emphasis id="82F7EACFFF87FFB3FDAEBBFDFCDAF85B" box="[632,780,1988,2012]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">M. hubeiensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D4124B2CFF87FFB3FCC4BBFDFC19F85B" author="Zheng, F. Q. &amp; Shi, J. P. &amp; Dang, Y." box="[786,975,1988,2012]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="198 - 200" refId="ref2446" refString="Zheng, F. Q., Shi, J. P. &amp; Dang, Y. (2017) A new species of the genus Mongolotettix Rehn, 1928 from Hubei, China (Acrididae, Acridoidea, Orthoptera). Zootaxa, 4250 (2), 198 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4250.2.6" type="journal article" year="2017">
Zheng 
<emphasis id="82F7EACFFF87FFB3FC8ABBFDFC5CF85B" box="[860,906,1988,2012]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">et al</emphasis>
, 2017
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The major differences are listed in 
<tableCitation id="FD010366FF87FFB3FA91BBFDFA40F85B" box="[1351,1430,1988,2012]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of Mongolotettix shandongensis sp. nov. and M. hubeiensis Zheng et al, 2017" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/E4FC6655FF85FFB1FF41BCAEFB00FF37" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" tableUuid="E4FC6655FF85FFB1FF41BCAEFB00FF37">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
